The joint statement outlines the meeting between Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and US President Barack Obama in June 2016. They reviewed the strategic partnership between the two countries and pledged to pursue opportunities for economic growth, sustainable development, peace and security, inclusive governance, and human rights. They also discussed their commitment to combating climate change and promoting clean energy. The leaders welcomed the progress made in bilateral relations and highlighted the importance of cooperation in areas such as defense, space, science and technology, and trade. They also emphasized the need to work together against terrorism and violent extremism, strengthen global nonproliferation efforts, and enhance people-to-people ties between the two countries.